ISLAMABAD, Jun 16 (APP): Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign Minister, Senator Mohammad Ishaq Dar on Monday received a high-level United Arab Emirates (UAE) delegation led by Deputy Minister of Cabinet Affairs for Competitiveness and Knowledge Exchange, Abdullah Nasser Lootah.
Appreciating the positive trajectory of Pakistan-UAE fraternal relations, they exchanged views on further strengthening bilateral cooperation in the areas of governance, institutional development, and public sector innovation.
